Amazon SQS - Simple Queue Service
What is Amazon SQS?
Amazon Simple Queue Service(SQS) is a message queuing service for communicating between software components. It sends, stores, and receives messages at any scale, ensuring messages arenot lost even when services are temporarily unavailable.

How it works
An application places messages into a queue. A user or service retrieves the message, processes it, and removes it from the queue. Subscribers can be web apps, servers, Lambda functions, and more.

